Logs grow really fast. It would be great if users get ability to chose what will be logged on the log file without loosing precious information needed on troubleshooting issues.

{{com.atlassian.jira.issue.attachment.TemporaryAttachment}}

{noformat}
    @Override
    public int hashCode()
    {
        int result = id.hashCode();
        result = 31 * result + tempAttachment.hashCode();
        result = 31 * result + filename.hashCode();
        result = 31 * result + contentType.hashCode();
        result = 31 * result + issueId.hashCode(); <- NPE
        result = 31 * result + created.hashCode();
        return result;
    }

    public String toString()
    {
        return ToStringBuilder.reflectionToString(this, ToStringStyle.SHORT_PREFIX_STYLE);
    }
{noformat}

hashCode() will throw an NPE if called on the TemporaryAttachment while creating an issue. It prevents plugin developers from putting a TemporaryAttachments in sets, maps, etc. You should use HashCodeBuilder, just like you used ToStringBuilder.

